### Create user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Testi Kayttaja",
  "username": "testi125",
  "email": "testi125@example.com",
  "password": "salasana123",
  "role": "user"
}

### Login
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testi125",
  "password": "salasana123"
}

### Save token from login response (REST Client)
@token = {{login.response.body.$.token}}
@userId = {{login.response.body.$.user.user_id}}

### Get current user info with token
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update logged-in user
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Testi Kayttaja Paivitetty",
  "username": "testi125",
  "email": "testi125@example.com",
  "role": "user"
}

### Create cat for logged-in user
# @name createCat
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cat_name": "Testi Kissa",
  "birthdate": "2020-01-01",
  "weight": 4.2,
  "owner": {{userId}}
}

### Save cat id from create cat response
@catId = {{createCat.response.body.$.cat_id}}

### Get cats by user id
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats/user/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update logged-in user's cat
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats/{{catId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Testi Kissa Paivitetty",
  "birthdate": "2020-01-01",
  "weight": 4.5,
  "owner": {{userId}}
}

### Delete logged-in user's cat
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats/{{catId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Error test: create user with empty body
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Error test: create cat with empty body
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Error test: upload invalid file type (replace path with an existing .txt file)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/cats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary123

--Boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cat_name"

Bad File Cat
--Boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="birthdate"

2020-01-01
--Boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="weight"

3.5
--Boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="owner"

{{userId}}
--Boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cat"; filename="bad.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

not an image or video
--Boundary123--

### Error test: upload file over 10 MB (replace path/content with large file payload)
# Use Postman form-data for this test to easily attach a >10MB file in the "cat" field.